Comments: I am very disappointed in your decision to not allow schools to have choice in what they offer parents at their book fairs.  I will no longer be offering flyers to my students.  I came to the site to suspend my account.

My willingness to recommend Schoolastic Book Clubs to a friend and to continue to support books fairs depends on it.

It was helpful for me to be able to choose my due date so that I could work the delivery of items around our school calendar.      Overall...I am not a fan of the changes that have been made this year and the limitations Scholastic has put on the teachers.  I am trying to decide whether to continue to offer this resource to my families.    After being a loyal supporter for over 20 years, this is such a   disappointment.

I am a long-time customer of Scholastic as an educator for over 40 years and now as a grandparent. I have also worked Scholastic bookfairs at schools. I understand the need to raise book prices but the selection of books from the book clubs and at the fairs is far less than in previous years including just last year. At the recent bookfair at my granddaughter's school, there were many hardcover books offered but not purchased. In addition there were many fur covered journals and organizers that also did not sell.  There were very few books for kids who brought $5 or $10 to the fair. Parents are struggling to make ends meet and it is disappointing to send kids home without a book when they brought too little money. I am hoping this is a temporary change. Please consider sending more cool deal/special low price books to the fairs and cut down on the hardcover books which are not affordable for most kids.

The search function is terrible - it gives imprecise results and sometimes leaves out results that should be included. I've been ordering for three years and the site never fails to frustrate.    Also frustrating is the lack of detail in the book descriptions. This is particularly egregious with packs of books. There is almost never a list of titles that are included or their number in a series. This means that you can't be sure you're not ordering duplicates without looking at each book cover in a pack and trying to compare to what you already have. A prime example is the Bad Guys series. In one pack, books #1-10 were included. Then, I went to buy the next set and tried to compare covers because no numbers are on the covers. I apparently wasn't careful enough and the next set was books #9-16. A simple list of the books included plus their number in the series would have resolved this, but so would not duplicating books in packs. This all seems very basic, so it's incredibly irritating

Now it seems Scholastic offers mostly "fad" books--Paw Patrol, Hot Wheels, Gabby's Dollhouse, etc...  Children need exposure to good, quality literature.  Plus your website is so confusing to navigate.  It used to be extremely easy to place orders.  I do not order near as frequently as I used to and honestly have considered giving up Scholastic all together.  I am sorry to write such a negative review, however I hope that it will be read and considered as I would like to continue business with Scholastic.

I feel like Scholastic is changing by not offering coupons or not as many  low priced books like they used too.  As an educator, and a member of Scholastics over the past 20+ years, I have used your company to provide books for my students individually or in my classroom library.  I have used the coupons as gifts for students  ($2 to purchase a $5 or less choice) .  This year I was informed that you don’t provide those coupons anymore.  Although I realize inflation is affecting everything, the rising cost really makes it more challenging for me to continue to provide as many books for students as I have in the past.  I usually always purchase “Charlotte’s Web” for each student as a gift after reading it as a class,  but for $5.99 each, I am saddened because I won’t be able yo afford that for 24 kids.  🥲  I do love your company and have appreciated the rewards from the points in book clubs!  It has also been helpful in adding to my library with the bonus points redemption!  I wouldn’t have such an extensive classroom library without it!    Thank you for all you do to encourage reading & helping  the community (teachers , like me) to getting books in hands of children! I have sure appreciated this company over the years as an educator!  The Book Club  have been wonderful in helping me to create students that love reading.  The “Branches” book that provide chapters from various books was a fantastic idea & I use it yearly as I introduce these series to my students!  It really helps to get them excited about reading chapter books!    Thank you for all you do to help encourage life-long learners & engaged readers!
